# Rivers endpoint

FTS_URL: `FTS_URL=https://fts.podaac.earthdata.nasa.gov/v1/rivers`

The rivers endpoint queries geospatial river data from the [SWOT River Database (SWORD)](https://www.swordexplorer.com/). Please see each section for example requests and responses for each query type for the rivers end point.

Please see [User Guide: Responses](/user-guide/responses) for more information on the response data common to all requests that gets returned.

## reaches

Example URL: `https://fts.podaac.earthdata.nasa.gov/v1/rivers/reach/66120000013`

Python requests library example:

```python
reach_identifier = '66120000013'
query_url = f'{FTS_URL}/reach/{reach_identifier}'
response = requests.get(query_url)
```

The reach response returns reach data in the `results` attribute for the reach identifier defined in the request. The fields that are returned are taken from the SWORD shapefile data. Sample response:


### reaches (all reaches in a basin)

Example URL: `https://fts.podaac.earthdata.nasa.gov/v1/rivers/reach/711817`

Python requests library example:

```python
basin_identifier = '711817'
query_url = f'{FTS_URL}/rivers/reach/{basin_identifier}'
response = requests.get(query_url)
```

The reach response returns reach data in the `results` attribute for all reaches associated with the basin identifier defined in the request. The fields that are returned are taken from the SWORD shapefile data. Sample response:

### river name (reaches only)

Example URL: `https://fts.podaac.earthdata.nasa.gov/v1/rivers/Ohio%20River?nodes=false&page_size=10&page_number=1`

*The river name query for reaches only must include a `page_size` and `page_number` query parameter to prevent a timeout. Please see [User Guide: Responses](/user-guide/pagination) for a description on how to use these parameters.*

The `nodes=false` query parameter is appended to the URL to remove nodes from the search results.

Python requests library example:

```python
river_name = 'Ohio River'
query_url = f'{FTS_URL}/rivers/{river_name}'
params={'nodes': 'false', 'page_size': 10, 'page_number': 1}
response = requests.get(query_url, params=params)
```
